{
  "texts": [
    "Automated essay scoring (AES) systems represent computerized tools adept at evaluating essays and allocating scores.",
    "By harnessing text processing, natural language processing, and machine learning algorithms to assess essay quality, these systems streamline the grad-ing process, offering benefits to both writers and evaluators.",
    "Through expediting grading procedures, providing prompt feedback, and mitigating grading inconsistencies, AES systems play a pivotal role in enhancing the efficiency and effectiveness of essay evaluation tasks (Williamson et al. 1999; Smolentzov 2013).",
    "AES aims to replicate the role of human evaluators but approaches the scoring process differently.",
    "Human evaluators follow rubric guidelines where a score and its associated essay quality attributes are defined."
  ]
}